or":false,"textReviewsCount":116,"viewableName":"Doug Cannon","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/901901-doug-cannon","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":24},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.jDDD-dHXtEsA77MEXMeNzA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.jDDD-dHXtEsA77MEXMeNzA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.-p-fK_M3pJzaFA9H4LFp4A"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:901901"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1641439510137,"createdAt":1202940583000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1345731408000,"text":"Grisham has a way of writing a real page-turner. This was one of those books that I just couldn't put down. The suspense was intense, and the story was good.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eWhen I finished the last page, and I finally did put it down, I couldn't help thinking I had just wasted my time. I mean, I was thoroughly entertained for every minute of the book, but when I was done, I was left with nothing but the memories of my entertainment.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eGood book, excellent author, but lacking in anything real. I've read 4 Grisham novels... sometimes I just want to be entertained, I guess. If that's what you're looking for, then Grisham is your man. Pick any of his books. They're all the same.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe movie was okay. This is probably one of Grisham's weaker books, but I'm not that good of a judge. If you want 2 hours of great entertainment, watch the movie. If you want more than that, read the book. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eJust like Grisham's novels, each of my reviews of his novels is almost identical to the last with only certain details changed to give it a new flavor.\u003cbr /\u003eGo ahead Grisham, sue me. Then, you can write a story about it.","rating":2,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/901901?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/15352415"},"likeCount":44,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":30,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:16731747":{"id":16731747,"__typename":"User","legacyId":16731747,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1436384393i/16731747._UY200_CR50,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":3721,"viewableName":"Calista","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/16731747-calista","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":31272},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.7OHxNlbEZ7UMeEfb07-OXA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.7OHxNlbEZ7UMeEfb07-OXA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.-p-fK_M3pJzaFA9H4LFp4A"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:16731747"},"recommendFor":"Legal thrillers, John Grisham Fans","updatedAt":1631997830160,"createdAt":1431912841000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1607224494531,"text":"John Grisham's 'the Firm' was what really got into reading novels over 300 pages. The story gripped me and got me over my fear of so many pages. So, I kept reading John's first 8 books or so as they were published.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI remember reading this in 1995 and loving the tough as nails lawyer of Reggie. I appreciated how she called people by their first names when they weren't used to it to level the playing field. She helps a kid in a tough situation. John has a gift for making the law exciting and dramatic. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI saw the movie and thought that Susan Sarandon was perfect in the movie. John was really on a hot streak here and it catapulted him into the big leagues. I stopped reading him after a while, but I suspect he is still an very entertaining read. I did read the Camino series 1st book about a book seller and that was a whole lot of fun.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI used to own all of these 8 book in hardback and some even were signed by Grisham. He is the only book signing I've been too and it was in my home town in 1994 at a mall when a mall still had bookstores in them. When I moved to Baltimore, I donated my Grisham books to the library so I no longer have any copies. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIf you are looking for a quick legal thriller or a page turning book, this would be a good one, but I would start with the Firm, next, the Pelican Brief and then this one. ","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16731747?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"genre-thriller","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16731747?shelf=genre-thriller"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"award-various","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16731747?shelf=award-various"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"bage-mature","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16731747?shelf=bage-mature"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"z-john-grisham","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16731747?shelf=z-john-grisham"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"1993","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16731747?shelf=1993"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1282954454"},"likeCount":40,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":14,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.bT9RE5MJDbtTRjZsuLn77Q":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.bT9RE5MJDbtTRjZsuLn77Q","__typename":"Book"},"User:614778":{"id":614778,"__typename":"User","legacyId":614778,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1194930432i/614778.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":9467,"viewableName":"Ahmad Sharabiani","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/614778-ahmad-sharabiani","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":53914},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.uXtgy8Md9eIXRKnE2dDZHQ":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.uXtgy8Md9eIXRKnE2dDZHQ","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.bT9RE5MJDbtTRjZsuLn77Q"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:614778"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1623595356617,"createdAt":1354004862000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1520937638338,"text":"The Client, John Grisham\u003cbr /\u003eThe Client (1993) is a legal thriller written by American author John Grisham, set mostly in Memphis, Tennessee and New Orleans, Louisiana. It is Grisham's fourth novel.\u003cbr /\u003eتاریخ نخستین خوانش: ماه اکتبر سال 2009 میلادی\u003cbr /\u003eعنوان: موکل؛ نویسنده: جان گریشام؛ مترجم: هادی عادلپور؛ تهران، کوشش، 1373؛ در 512 ص؛ \u003cbr /\u003eعنوان: موکل خطرناک؛ نویسنده: جان گریشام؛ مترجم: محمد قصاع؛ تهران، البرز، 1373؛ در 472 ص؛: \u003cbr /\u003eعنوان: موکل؛ نویسنده: جان گریشام؛ مترجم: قیطاس مردانی راد؛ تهران، سروش، 1376؛ در 623 ص؛ شابک: 9644352866؛\u003cbr /\u003eکتاب «موکل»، با عنوان «موکل خطرناک»، در: 473 صفحه، توسط نشر البرز نیز، منتشر شده است. داستان درباره «مایک» پسرکی یازده ساله، و برادرش «ریکی» است که ناخواسته شاهد خودکشی مردی در علفزارهای کنار خانه خویش هستند، «مایک» به دلیل شرایط سخت زندگی، خود را پشتیبان مادر، و برادر کوچکترش میداند، او برای نجات مرد نیز سعی میکند، اما، گیر میافتد. مرد تصمیم میخواهد که در پایان لحظات عمرش، تنها به سوی مرگ نرود، او میخواهد «مایک» نیز، همراهش باشد. مرد از راز قتل یکی از سناتورهای امریکایی، توسط موکل خویش پرده برمیدارد، و به «مایک» میگوید: موکلش جنازه آن سناتور را، که کل ایالت به دنبالش هستند، زیر پارکینگ خانه او، دفن کرده است! از آن لحظه به بعد، «مایک» اطلاعاتی پیدا میکند، که زندگی کودکانه و ساده او را، وا